---
page_title: Checkbox
description: Checkboxes are most commonly used to give users a way to make a range of selections (zero, one, or multiple).

layout: content
index: true
---

.content
  h1.bx--type-h1 = current_page.data.page_title
  p.bx--type-p
    | Checkboxes are most commonly used to give users a way to make a range of selections (zero, one, or multiple). They can be used:
    ul.e-list
      li When a user can select any number of choices from a set list.
      li When users need to see all the available options at a glance.

  .content-block
    h2.bx--type-h4.u-text-blue States
    p.bx--type-p
      | These are the different states you can find the checkbox component.

    .row.u-py-7.col-xs-offset-0.col-lg-offset-1
      .col-xs-12.col-sm-6.col-md-3
        = partial :"components/_checkbox", :locals => { :checked => false, :label_selected => 'Default', :label_unselected => 'Default' }
      .col-xs-12.col-sm-6.col-md-3
        = partial :"components/_checkbox", :locals => { :checked => true, :label_selected => 'Selected', :label_unselected => 'Unselected' }
      .col-xs-12.col-sm-6.col-md-3
        = partial :"components/_checkbox", :locals => { :disabled => true, :checked => false, :label_selected => 'Disabled', :label_unselected => 'Disabled' }
      .col-xs-12.col-sm-6.col-md-3
        = partial :"components/_checkbox", :locals => { :multiple => true, :checked => false, :label_selected => 'Multiple check', :label_unselected => 'Multiple check' }

  .clipboard
    h4.bx--type-h4.u-text-blue.uppercase  Code/Html > Save
    .code-wrapper
      .code-content id="checkbox-code"
        = code("html") do
          | <div class="lds--custom-input checkbox">
              <input class="lds--checkbox-input" id="52" name="set-name" type="checkbox">
              <label class="lds--checkbox-label" for="52">
                <span class="label-on bx--type-label selected"> Default</span>
                <span class="label-off bx--type-label">Default</span>
              </label>
            </div>

      = partial :"components/_code_actions", :locals => { :target => '#checkbox-code'}

  .content-block
    = partial :"blocks/_anatomy", :locals => { :extracolumn => true, :item => data.component_slider.items.checkbox }

  .content-block
    h2.bx--type-h4.u-text-blue Spacing
    p.bx--type-p
      | The vertical spacing starts from the path limit of the longest option. For more than three options, the checkboxes should be disposed in:

    ul.e-list
      li Mobile: 1 column
      li Tablet: 2 - 4 columns
      li Desktop: 2 - 4 - 8 columns
    p.bx--type-p.u-pt-2
      | You can find more info about the column system in the #{link_to 'Layout page', '/guidelines/layout.html', class: 'blue-link'}.

  .content-block.examples-layout
